{"name": "gentrade", "metadata": {"name": "gentrade", "version": "0.0.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["wheel"], "summary": "GenAI based Trading Package", "upload_time": 1734009188}, "documentation": ["# GenTrade\n\nThe python GenTrade package provide the core functions, model and data to support\nGenAI based algorithms trading.\n\n\n![](./docs/overview.png)\n\nFor a quick testing, please\n\n- Install the python package\n\n  ```\n  pip install gentrade\n  ```\n\n- Then try:\n\n  - [Demos](./demo/): command line based app to show market OHLCV data\n  - [Tests](./tests/): test cases for the API and utilities\n  - [Apps](./apps/): the application or microservices based on gentrade.\n\n\n## App and Services\n\n### OHLCV Data Service\n\n- Start Server\n\n  ```shell\n  # Pull image\n  docker pull registry.cn-hangzhou.aliyuncs.com/kenplusplus/gentrade_data_serv\n\n  # Create .env file from .env_template\n\n  # Run OHLCV datahub service\n  docker run -p 8000:8000 \\\n      --env-file=.env -v <data folder>:/app/cache \\\n      registry.cn-hangzhou.aliyuncs.com/kenplusplus/gentrade_data_serv\n  ```\n\n- Client Test\n\n  ```shell\n\n  # Get all supported markets\n  curl -X 'GET' \\\n    'http://127.0.0.1:8000/markets/?market_type=all' \\\n    -H 'accept: application/json'\n\n  # Get all available assets from a specific market\n  curl -X 'GET' \\\n    'http://127.0.0.1:8000/assets/?market_id=b13a4902-ad9d-11ef-a239-00155d3ba217&start=0&max_count=1000' \\\n    -H 'accept: application/json'\n\n  # Get OHLCV for a specific asset\n  curl -X 'GET' \\\n    'http://127.0.0.1:8000/asset/get_ohlcv?market_id=b13a4902-ad9d-11ef-a239-00155d3ba217&asset=BTC_USDT&timeframe=1m&since=-1&limit=10' \\\n    -H 'accept: application/json'\n\n  # Start OHLCV collector threading in the background\n  curl -X 'POST' \\\n    'http://127.0.0.1:8000/asset/start_collect?market_id=b13a4902-ad9d-11ef-a239-00155d3ba217&asset=DOGE_USDT&timeframe=1h&since=1732809600' \\\n    -H 'accept: application/json' \\\n    -d ''\n  ```\n\nThe cached data can be found at [this directory](./cache/)\n"], "modules": [{"name": "gentrade", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "gentrade.market_data", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic", "documentation": ["The collections of basic strategies"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.LOG", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyBase", "bases": ["bt.Strategy"], "methods": [{"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyBase.log", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "txt", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "dt", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyBase.notify_order", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "order", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyBase.notify_trade", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "trade", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["pylint: disable=no-member, too-many-function-args, unexpected-keyword-arg"]}, {"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyRsi", "bases": ["StrategyBase"], "methods": [{"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyRsi.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyRsi.next", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyRsi.params", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategySma", "bases": ["StrategyBase"], "methods": [{"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategySma.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategySma.next", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategySma.params", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["SMA, SimpleMovingAverage\nNon-weighted average of the last n periods\n\nFormula:\n    movav = Sum(data, period) / period\n\nSee also:\n    http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moving_average#Simple_moving_average"]}, {"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyMacd", "bases": ["StrategyBase"], "methods": [{"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyMacd.log", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "txt", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "dt", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Logging function for this strategy"]}, {"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyMacd.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyMacd.next", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyMacd.params", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyWma", "bases": ["StrategyBase"], "methods": [{"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyWma.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyWma.next", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyWma.params", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Alias:\n\n    WMA, MovingAverageWeighted\n    A Moving Average which gives an arithmetic weighting to values with the\n    newest having the more weight\n\nFormula:\n\n    weights = range(1, period + 1)\n    coef = 2 / (period * (period + 1))\n    movav = coef * Sum(weight[i] * data[period - i] for i in range(period))\n\nSee also:\n\n    http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moving_average#Weighted_moving_average"]}, {"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyBb", "bases": ["StrategyBase"], "methods": [{"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyBb.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyBb.next", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "gentrade.strategy.basic.StrategyBb.params", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["BollingerBands\n\nDefined by John Bollinger in the 80s. It measures volatility by defining\nupper and lower bands at distance x standard deviations\n\nFormula:\n    midband = SimpleMovingAverage(close, period)\n    topband = 